    "content": "nullSalesforce B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Salesforce B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\n Commerce Basics\n Get Started with Salesforce Commerce\n Import and Export Commerce Data\n Access to Commerce Stores\n Products and Pricing\n Configure Checkout for a Commerce Store\n Store Search\n Search Engine Optimization (SEO) for Commerce\n Commerce Einstein\n Einstein and Data Usage in Commerce Cloud\n Data Cloud for Commerce\n Store Management\n Commerce Promotions\n Considerations for Commerce Promotions\n Configure a Promotion\n Create a Promotion\n Create a Promotion Using a Template\n Create Promotions with Einstein\n Target Customers with a Promotion Segment\n Add a Promotion Tier\n Create a Coupon\n Define a Promotion Discount\n Choose What Qualifies for a Promotion\n Set Conditional Rules for a Promotion\n Localize Promotion Data\n Customize Promotions in Experience Builder\n Promotions in Checkout for B2B (Aura) Stores\n Example Promotions\n Prioritizing Promotions\n Remove a Promotion\n Sell Globally\n Website Design for Commerce Stores\n Publication and Activation\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nB2B COMMERCE AND D2C COMMERCE\nAdd a Promotion Tier\n\nUse promotion tiers to create progressive discounts for a promotion. Apply the highest qualifying tier to a cart. You can add tiers only to a promotion that was created as a tiered promotion. All discounts within a tier must be of the same type. You can create up to 10 tiers per promotion.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: Lightning Experience\nAvailable in: Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions\nAvailable in: B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\nIMPORTANT As of Summer ’24, there’s a refreshed Commerce app, which we encourage you to use. The navigation steps in this Help documentation reflect the new app. If you’re still using the previous app, now called the Commerce Storefront Console, see B2B and D2C Commerce Using the Commerce Storefront Console. For instructions on switching to the refreshed app, see Enable the Refreshed Commerce App.\nIMPORTANT Tiers can only be used for promotions that were created as tiered promotions.\nIn the navigation sidebar, select a store from the Store dropdown.\nClick Promotions.\nSelect the tiered promotion.\nOn the Tiers tab, click New.\nEnter a promotion tier name.\nSelect the promotion you want the tier to be assigned to.\nEnter a rank.\nThe rank determines which tier applies first. The lower the number, the better the discount.\nClick Save.\nNavigate to the promotion tier and select the Related tab.\nTo add discount details for the tier, click New next to Discounts. See Define Promotion Discounts.\nTo add qualifier details for the tier, click New next to Promotion Qualifiers. See Choose What Qualifies for a Promotion.\nRepeat these steps to create each tier.\nEXAMPLE To entice shoppers to purchase more, you want to give a better discount as the shopper adds more to their cart. You create three promotion tiers that give the shopper 10% off a $50 purchase, 20% off a $100 purchase, or 30% off a $200 purchase. When you create your promotion, select Tiered Promotion and then:\nCreate a tier for each discount level and associate it with the tiered promotion.\nAssign the best discount to the lowest rank.\nAdd your discounts and promotion qualifiers to each tier.\nSEE ALSO\nCommerce Promotions\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
